Test Plan

Purpose:
- Public-safe current test and verification memory for the MemoryEndpoints.com enterprise MATM gate.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify by running the commands named here before relying on it.
Memory scope: local test gates, integration proof, report refresh order, and completion-blocking verification.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file when required verification changes; submit durable public-safe test summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `tests/`, `scripts/verify_memoryendpoints.py`, `scripts/dogfood_memoryendpoints.py`, `scripts/enterprise_readiness_audit.py`, and `docs/verification.md`.
Next action for agents: run the full local gate after material code or memory changes and refresh reports before committing.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, raw one-time keys, private handoff payloads, raw logs, or local runtime database contents.

Current local gate:
- `python -m unittest discover -s tests`
- `python scripts\verify_memoryendpoints.py --wsgi --expect-git-head --json-out docs\reports\local-route-verification.json`
- `python scripts\verify_static_site.py --json-out docs\reports\multiagentmemory-static-site-verification.json`
- `python scripts\audit_uai_memory.py --json-out docs\reports\uai-memory-audit.json`
- `python scripts\audit_repository_boundary.py --json-out docs\reports\repository-boundary-audit.json`
- `python scripts\package_memoryendpoints.py --json-out docs\reports\package-verification-report.json`
- `python scripts\secret_scan.py --json-out docs\reports\secret-scan-report.json`
- `python scripts\enterprise_readiness_audit.py --run-checks --json-out docs\reports\enterprise-readiness-audit.json`
- `python scripts\build_readiness_reports.py --write`
- `git diff --check`
- Deploy dry-run evidence must match the package report and remain a no-upload safe no-op before any live deploy claim.

External evidence refresh:
- GitHub Actions is not a completion gate and must not be retried unless the human explicitly re-enables it.
- Pushed-source proof comes from the remote branch and exact live `build.sourceSha` verification, followed by live route, MySQL, package, and dogfood checks.
- Tracked readiness reports are point-in-time snapshots. Treat local route, package, and live latest-code report files as stale standalone evidence when their recorded source SHA does not match the Git HEAD being evaluated; use fresh no-write commands after commit or push as the current-commit proof.

Coverage expectations:
- Single-report ingestion tests must prove canonical source preflight, exact replay idempotency, body-derived revision fingerprints, data-image omission, distinct source/selection/indexed-content hashes, reviewer-authored overlay provenance, explicit stops across unfenced embedded headings, structured query-identifier redaction, and report self-scan failure on raw credentials or scope identifiers.
- Single-link ingestion tests must prove canonical-URL preflight, exact replay versus changed-metadata revision behavior, citation attachment detection, exact metadata readback, canonical language/content-type/crawl-policy handling, preservation of an existing explicit canonical review disposition when an unreviewed mention is added, and public-safe report redaction.
- Single-memory review tests must prove ingestion-report selection of exactly one event, direct/report mismatch rejection, accepted-pending promotion gates, invalid transition rejection, idempotent already-decided handling, hashed review notes, tenant-identifier redaction, and protected state readback.
- Every completed source cycle must verify exact document count, one canonical source identity, exact source and selected-section hashes, title/description/keywords/multiple taxonomy paths, lifecycle reasons, canonical-link and mention counts, one promoted memory per page, no invalid durable scope, database-only search/tree/link results, anonymous API denial, empty signed-out deep-route content, authenticated wiki navigation, responsive layout, and browser diagnostics.
- Discoverability-source verification must separate historical observation from fresh reachability; reject impossible access dates as current evidence; classify DNS, TLS, redirect, HTTP, media-type, parse, browser-CORS, and authentication failures independently; and link product conventions to current primary protocol sources before promoting a reviewed conclusion.
- Route handler integration tests must exercise public discovery and protected MATM workflows.
- Private-knowledge tests must enumerate the wiki tree, document, external-link, internet-search, and project routes; prove anonymous requests are safe `401` no-ops; prove a valid key cannot select another workspace; and prove failed re-authentication clears the rendered private wiki.
- Protected deep-link tests must prove only company, workspace, and project wiki paths receive the empty private shell; account, user, goal, task, malformed, and unsupported routes return `404`; exact route lookup remains workspace-bound; signed-out deep routes reveal no tenant content; and authenticated internal Markdown links, direct navigation, modified-click behavior, and browser back navigation preserve the private wiki contract.
- Review-filter tests must prove source, tag, memory-type, and actor filters retain redacted metadata for pending, promoted, rejected, and quarantined review records while rejected and quarantined memory remains absent from normal search; file, SQLite, and production MySQL paths must preserve the same boundary.
- Hierarchy tests must prove account-company membership is many-to-many while durable knowledge rejects account, user, goal, and task scopes and accepts only company, workspace, and project.
- Public route and companion-site verifiers must report zero secret hits and zero public leak hits for local filesystem paths, file URIs, or raw traceback fragments.
- Public discovery and signed-out wiki checks must prove the home page, robots, LLM orientation, manifests, and unauthenticated deep-route shell contain no protected title, source prefix, tenant identifier, or company/workspace/project deep route.
- Repository boundary audit must prove there are no duplicate MemoryEndpoints.com or MultiAgentMemory.com active site folders at the drive root and no root-level runtime artifacts such as local SQLite write checks or devserver logs.
- Storage tests must prove one-time workspace keys are persisted only as hashes, raw keys are absent from file and SQLite storage, SQLite relational tables exist, memory revisions are represented, and the active tested path does not rely on a single JSON blob table.
- Dogfood must create or use a workspace, register an agent, submit/search memory, create/read/ack current messages, read receipts, read audit log, generate a redacted report, and update `.uai` progress without dates.
